E. COLI EHEC - USA (19): (MINNESOTA) COUNTY FAIRS
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 12 Aug 2014
Source: KIMT TV3 [edited]
http://kimt.com/2014/08/12/e-coli-outbreak-linked-to-petting-zoo-in-minnesota/


Minnesota Department of Health is warning people about _E. coli_ infections linked to a traveling petting zoo. At least 13 people, including 3 in Olmsted County, have developed _E. coli_ [O157] infections in an outbreak connected to the Zerebko Zoo Tran petting zoo. Those infected, range in age from 2 to 68 years old and 7 of them have been hospitalized, including 3 children.

The most recent appearance of the Zerebko petting zoo was at the Olmsted County Fair from 21 through 27 Jul 2014. Authorities say the zoo owner has been cooperating with their investigation, and withheld his animals from the last 2 county fairs where they were going to be exhibited. Infections have also been traced to the zoo's stops at the Nashwauk 4th of July Festival, the Polk County Fair, and the Rice County Fair.

State Public Health Veterinarian Dr Joni Scheftel says _E. coli_ "can be present in even the cleanest of animal operations." State health officials says they are currently following up with one more case, and additional infections associated with attending the Olmsted County Fair could still be identified.

[Byline: Mike Bunge]

